.TH lpshut "" "" Command
.PC "Turn off the printer daemon despooler"
\fBlpshut [\-d]\fR
.PP
.HS
Option \fB\-d\fR tells \fBlpshut\fR to finish currently printing jobs
.HE
The command
.B lpshut
turns off the printer daemon
.BR lpsched .
.PP
The option
.B \-d
tells
.B lpshut
to finish the jobs that are currently printing
before it shuts down the daemon.
If jobs are interrupted while printing, the printer daemon
.B lpsched
reprints them when it restarts.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "commands," commands
.Xr "lp," lp
.Xr "lpsched," lpsched
.Xr "printer" printer

